Delaware Special Purpose Entities





 
								 
									
								
									Print
								
							
						 





   When experience and reputation count  





Wells Fargo offers Delaware Statutory Trust services and other Delaware special purpose entities, such as limited liability companies, limited partnerships and corporations, as part of a comprehensive suite of corporate trust products and services from our Wilmington, Del., office. When you work with us, you’ll benefit from:   Experience and reputation. We are a leading provider of Delaware Statutory Trust services with 75 years of experience. Dedicated account teams. Enjoy the simplicity and convenience of a team knowledgeable of the nuances of your transaction. Online reporting. Our technology and reporting tools let you easily monitor the details of your transactions. Complementary services. We can offer you additional services such as cash management, and can act as an administrative agent, escrow agent, custodian, or disbursement agent. Our global Wells Fargo network. Wells Fargo is the leading U.S. bank provider of trade, payments, foreign exchange, deposit, and other services to financial institutions around the globe. With offices in the U.S., 35 locations overseas, and a network of financial institution partners around the world, we provide customer coverage in 130 countries.  Use Delaware special purpose entities for the following transactions:  Asset-backed securitizations Transportation finance Life settlement and premium finance Titling trusts Mortgage-backed securities Structured note programs Project and renewable energy finance 






 Contact us  Rosemary Kennard, VP  Business Negotiations Consultant  302-575-2002  rosemary.kennard@wellsfargo.com Jose Mercado, VP  Business Negotiations Consultant  302-575-2001  jose.i.mercado@wellsfargo.com  
Additional information
Get information about your bearer and registered bonds or contact us at bondholdercommunications

@wellsfargo.com or 1-800-344-5128.




















